Popular social media influencer, Babatunde Olusola Thomas, popularly known as Shola Jayy The Dope has disclosed that he faced threats and attacks both online and offline for speaking against manipulative women. Shola is a leading voice of the “Alpha Male” movement, an online masculinity awareness aimed at raising high-value men. According to Shola Jayy The Dope, “men were dipping, most especially Nigerian men, the bar was getting lower, our men were normalizing simping, and a whole lot of great men have been falling also as a result of dealing with manipulative women, I just had to start the movement.” Auxell Musical shows love at  orphanage to mark St… Nigerian Idol Season 7: Toolz Joins D’banj, Obi Asika As Guest… The Chemical Engineering graduate of Ladoke Akintola University of Technology, (LAUTECH) further said many women took to the same social media to abuse and threaten him for moving against them. I get attacks and threats always, but these are mostly from low-quality women, the same set of women I talk against, the manipulative and extorting ones. “Funny thing is, most times I ignore them, sometimes I just want to use some of them as scapegoats. So I respond,” he added. Speaking about his relationship status, the 25-year-old life coach said he’s staying focused on himself for now. “I’m actually an ambitious person and the dream is too big, there’s still a long way to go, just don’t want any relationship distractions for now,” he stated.